import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['date'])]

    plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='values', bins=20, color='blue', kde=True)
    plt.axvline(data['values'].median(), color='red', linestyle='--', label=f"Median: {data['values'].median():.2f}")
    plt.legend()
    plt.title("What is the distribution of values in the dataset?", wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['date'])]

    plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))
    sns.lineplot(x='date', y='values_count', data=data)
    plt.title('How does the number of values change over time?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Date')
    plt.ylabel('Values Count')
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    plt.legend(['Values Count'])

    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
